{"title":"Tour of Britain Women 2024: Route, how to watch and everything you need to know","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-of-britain-women-preview","date":1717082510000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-of-britain-women-preview\">Tour of Britain Women 2024: Route, how to watch and everything you need to know</a></p>\n\n<p>The UK’s biggest stage race for the women’s peloton returns. The newly named Tour of Britain Women will take the crème de la crème of the women’s sport on a four-day long trail around Wales and northern England.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You are forgiven for missing the memo. This race was <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/womens-tour-2023\" target=\"_blank\">halted in 2023 due to financial constraints</a>. This year, however, the Tour of Britain Women has <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/tour-of-britain-women-2024-route\" target=\"_blank\">risen from the ashes under British Cycling’s organisation with a new monicker and a new identity</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The reigning champion Elisa Longo-Borghini will not be here to defend her crown. In fact, her Lidl-Trek squad will not compete at all at this year’s edition, with their home favourite Lizzie Deignan competing for a Great Britain Cycling Team in this race. The favourites will be within the SD Worx-ProTime camp. Lotte Kopecky, the current world champion, will start as the most-marked woman in the pack.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/danni-shrosbree-podcast\">Cyclist Magazine Podcast episode 106: Unbound Gravel 2024, racing with British champ Danni Shrosbree</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/ridelondon-classique-gallery-2024\">RideLondon Classique gallery: Wiebes’ World, party time, excellent</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/worldtour-race-ranked-women\">Every UCI Women’s WorldTour race ranked: From the Tour de France to the Tour of Chongming Island</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/tour-of-britain-women-2024-route\">From North Wales to Manchester: Tour of Britain Women announces route for 2024 race</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/lizzie-deignan-cyclist\">Lizzie Deignan Q&amp;A: ‘It was never a question of whether I would retire’</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2>Tour of Britain Women 2024: Key information</h2>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"547\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToB-Women-peloton-970x547.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToB-Women-peloton-970x547.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToB-Women-peloton-300x169.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToB-Women-peloton-768x433.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToB-Women-peloton-1536x867.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToB-Women-peloton-2048x1156.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToB-Women-peloton-750x423.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToB-Women-peloton-1140x643.jpg 1140w\" /><figcaption>British Cycling</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Date:</strong> 6th-9th June</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Start:</strong> Welshpool</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Finish:</strong> Leigh (Greater Manchester)</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Distance: </strong>488.5km</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Live UK TV coverage: </strong>Eurosport, Discovery+</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>2022 winner: </strong>Elisa Longo Borghini (Lidl-Trek)</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Tour of Britain Women 2024: Route and stage-by-stage preview</h2>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/Tour-of-Britain-970x647.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/Tour-of-Britain-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/Tour-of-Britain-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/Tour-of-Britain-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/Tour-of-Britain-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/Tour-of-Britain-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/Tour-of-Britain-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/Tour-of-Britain-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/Tour-of-Britain-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/Tour-of-Britain-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/Tour-of-Britain.jpg 2048w\" /><figcaption>British Cycling</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>This year’s Tour of Britain Women route will feature a total of four road stages — three of which have been teased as hilly affairs by the race organisers. There is no time-trial on offer in this race, but the winner crowned in Leigh will have to be a hardy all-rounder.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Wales plays host to the Grand Départ of the Tour of Britain Women and will be front and centre, hosting half of the stages on offer. The course sets out from Welshpool on day one with a finish in the old seaside town of Llandudno. The day after, the race rings around Wrexham, before crossing Offa’s Dyke into England for Stage 3. The final stage’s Mancunian hurrah will see the race snake around England’s second city, arriving in Leigh for the final podium celebrations.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 1: Welshpool – Llandudno, 146km</h3>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"331\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/stage-1-tob-women-oriofile-970x331.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/stage-1-tob-women-oriofile-970x331.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/stage-1-tob-women-oriofile-300x102.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/stage-1-tob-women-oriofile-768x262.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/stage-1-tob-women-oriofile-750x256.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/stage-1-tob-women-oriofile-1140x389.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/stage-1-tob-women-oriofile.png 1284w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>The opening stage takes the riders through the depths of North Wales. The day sets off from Welshpool, Montgomeryshire, making a northerly turn once the flag drops. The road will soon become hillier as the peloton negotiates the first climbs of the 2024 Tour of Britain Women. The toughest climb of the day, Llangynog (6.1km at 5.3%) arrives just before the halfway marker on the stage. </p>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"686\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToBW_Stage_1-Welshpool_to_Llandudno_PNG-970x686.webp\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToBW_Stage_1-Welshpool_to_Llandudno_PNG-970x686.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToBW_Stage_1-Welshpool_to_Llandudno_PNG-300x212.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToBW_Stage_1-Welshpool_to_Llandudno_PNG-768x543.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToBW_Stage_1-Welshpool_to_Llandudno_PNG-1536x1086.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToBW_Stage_1-Welshpool_to_Llandudno_PNG-120x86.webp 120w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToBW_Stage_1-Welshpool_to_Llandudno_PNG-750x530.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToBW_Stage_1-Welshpool_to_Llandudno_PNG-1140x806.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToBW_Stage_1-Welshpool_to_Llandudno_PNG.webp 1842w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>After the second categorised climb of Ty’n y Llindiart, the race will shoot down the Conwy river towards the stage’s finale in Llandudno. The arrival into the Welsh seaside resort is moderately flat, so expect a sprint for stage glory on day one of the 2024 Tour of Britain Women.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 2: Wrexham – Wrexham, 144.1km</h3>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"331\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/tob-women-sgage-2-porifle-970x331.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/tob-women-sgage-2-porifle-970x331.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/tob-women-sgage-2-porifle-300x102.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/tob-women-sgage-2-porifle-768x262.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/tob-women-sgage-2-porifle-750x256.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/tob-women-sgage-2-porifle-1140x389.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/tob-women-sgage-2-porifle.png 1266w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>Stage 2 rings around the Welsh town of Wrexham. The parcours moves into England after a handful of kilometres, funnelling the riders along flat and straight-forward roads. The stage returns over the Welsh border in time for the stage’s first category climb and intermediate sprint. The category 1 Horseshoe Pass (4.2km at 6.4%) comes at a crucial point in the stage, cresting out at the 25km to go marker. </p>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"686\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToBW_Stage_2-Wrexham_PNG-970x686.webp\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToBW_Stage_2-Wrexham_PNG-970x686.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToBW_Stage_2-Wrexham_PNG-300x212.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToBW_Stage_2-Wrexham_PNG-768x543.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToBW_Stage_2-Wrexham_PNG-1536x1086.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToBW_Stage_2-Wrexham_PNG-120x86.webp 120w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToBW_Stage_2-Wrexham_PNG-750x530.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToBW_Stage_2-Wrexham_PNG-1140x806.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToBW_Stage_2-Wrexham_PNG.webp 1842w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>From the peak of the climb, the race will turn down through the Clwydian Range &amp; Dee Valley AONB. The road will flatten out within the final five kilometres as the race arrives into Wrexham once again. The profile is open and unpredictable, so it’s hard to anticipate the weight this stage will have on the GC fight. Regardless, it will be a hard race to control for any team.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 3: Warrington – Warrington, 111.6km</h3>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"411\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/stage-3-tobwomen-profile-970x411.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/stage-3-tobwomen-profile-970x411.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/stage-3-tobwomen-profile-300x127.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/stage-3-tobwomen-profile-768x326.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/stage-3-tobwomen-profile-750x318.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/stage-3-tobwomen-profile.png 1021w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>Warrington hosts Stage 3 of the Tour of Britain Women. The day’s route will lasso around the north-western town, on a mostly flat profile. The profile will roll through picturesque Cheshire towns around the south Manchester suburbs of Wilmslow and Knutsford. Some climbs punctuate the route around halfway through, but their difficulty is negligible. </p>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"686\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToBW_Stage_3-Warrington-970x686.webp\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToBW_Stage_3-Warrington-970x686.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToBW_Stage_3-Warrington-300x212.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToBW_Stage_3-Warrington-768x543.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToBW_Stage_3-Warrington-1536x1086.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToBW_Stage_3-Warrington-120x86.webp 120w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToBW_Stage_3-Warrington-750x530.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToBW_Stage_3-Warrington-1140x806.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToBW_Stage_3-Warrington.webp 1842w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>The race’s arrival is flat and open. This should allow for a bullish battle for positions on the approach to Warrington. The final kilometres pose some technical difficulties, with a tight hairpin corner within the final kilometre. The sprinters will be out in their droves, hoping for the chance of Tour of Britain glory here in Warrington.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 4: Manchester – Leigh, 108.3km</h3>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"943\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/stage-4-profile-tob-women.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/stage-4-profile-tob-women.png 943w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/stage-4-profile-tob-women-300x136.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/stage-4-profile-tob-women-768x348.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/stage-4-profile-tob-women-750x340.png 750w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>The final stage of the 2024 edition offers a tough and relentless profile around Greater Manchester. The day begins at the National Cycling Centre in eastern Manchester. The race leaves the urban sprawl and heads into hilly periphery roads quickly. Grains Bar (2.4km at 5.8%) comes on the profile just under 20km from the start. The slopes continue at the Ramsbottom Rake (1.1km at 10.1%), a steep kicker in the outskirts of Bury. The final phase of the race snakes around the Lancashire foothills on a more moderate approach to the finishing town of Leigh.</p>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"686\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToBW_Stage_4-NCC_to_Leigh-970x686.webp\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToBW_Stage_4-NCC_to_Leigh-970x686.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToBW_Stage_4-NCC_to_Leigh-300x212.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToBW_Stage_4-NCC_to_Leigh-768x543.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToBW_Stage_4-NCC_to_Leigh-1536x1086.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToBW_Stage_4-NCC_to_Leigh-120x86.webp 120w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToBW_Stage_4-NCC_to_Leigh-750x530.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToBW_Stage_4-NCC_to_Leigh-1140x806.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/ToBW_Stage_4-NCC_to_Leigh.webp 1842w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>The stage’s hilly profile hands the GC contenders one last chance to shake up the standings. Equally, breakaway hopefuls may sniff out a chance to claim a stage win at the British race.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Tour of Britain Women 2024: How to watch</h2>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"646\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/05/GettyImages-womens-tour-peloton-2022-970x646.jpg\" alt=\"peloton of women cycling past classically british houses\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/05/GettyImages-womens-tour-peloton-2022-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/05/GettyImages-womens-tour-peloton-2022-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/05/GettyImages-womens-tour-peloton-2022-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/05/GettyImages-womens-tour-peloton-2022-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/05/GettyImages-womens-tour-peloton-2022-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/05/GettyImages-womens-tour-peloton-2022-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/05/GettyImages-womens-tour-peloton-2022-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/05/GettyImages-womens-tour-peloton-2022-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/05/GettyImages-womens-tour-peloton-2022-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/05/GettyImages-womens-tour-peloton-2022-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Justin Setterfield/Getty Images</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>The Tour of Britain Women will be shown live on <a href=\"https://www.discoveryplus.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Discovery+</a> in the UK and Europe. There is no live TV broadcasting scheduled as of yet in the UK or Europe. However, in the UK, hour-long highlights shows will be broadcast on free-to-air ITV4. These will be shown at 8pm each day of the race, from 6th June to 9th June. In North America, the racing will be available through FloBikes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If it’s not being shown in your country, you may be able to watch coverage using a VPN – Virtual Private Network – which allows users to mask their IP address and watch geo-blocked content, provided they don’t need to pay for a subscription. This is also helpful for watching paid-for coverage while travelling abroad in countries without access. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>One such example is <a href=\"https://go.expressvpn.com/m5yJGZ\" target=\"_blank\">ExpressVPN</a>, which is very <a href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/advisor/vpn/expressvpn-review\" target=\"_blank\">well reviewed</a>, has specific advice for watching cycling and costs £5.36 per month with three months free. Other options include <a href=\"https://go.skimresources.com/?id=205647X1684865&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fnordvpn.com%2F\" target=\"_blank\">NordVPN</a>, <a href=\"https://go.skimresources.com/?id=205647X1684865&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fsurfshark.com%2F\" target=\"_blank\">Surfshark</a> and <a href=\"https://go.skimresources.com/?id=205647X1684865&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kaspersky.co.uk%2F\" target=\"_blank\">Kapersky</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Read more: <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/how-to-watch-cycling\" target=\"_blank\">How to watch cycling post-GCN</a></strong> </li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Live TV and streaming times</h2>\n\n\n\n<p><em>All times BST and subject to change by broadcasters</em></p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Stage 1: Welshpool – Llandudno, Thursday 6th June</h4>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+:</strong> 12:00-14:00</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Stage 2: Wrexham – Wrexham, Friday 7th June</h4>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+:</strong> 12:00-14:00</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Stage 3: Warrington – Warrington, Saturday 8th June</h4>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+:</strong> 12:00-14:00</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Stage 4: Manchester – Leigh, Sunday 9th June</h4>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+:</strong> 12:00-14:00</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Tour of Britain Women 2024: Start list</h2>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Team line-ups are not yet fully confirmed, so the list is subject to change pre-race</em></p>\n\n\n\n<div><p><em>Data powered by <a href=\"https://firstcycling.com/race.php?r=9063&amp;y=2024&amp;k=8\" target=\"_blank\">FirstCycling.com</a></em></p></div>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/danni-shrosbree-podcast\">Cyclist Magazine Podcast episode 106: Unbound Gravel 2024, racing with British champ Danni Shrosbree</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/ridelondon-classique-gallery-2024\">RideLondon Classique gallery: Wiebes’ World, party time, excellent</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/worldtour-race-ranked-women\">Every UCI Women’s WorldTour race ranked: From the Tour de France to the Tour of Chongming Island</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/tour-of-britain-women-2024-route\">From North Wales to Manchester: Tour of Britain Women announces route for 2